<p><strong>Background:</strong><br />
Tevi Troy is a Senior Fellow at the Mercatus Center, a research center at George Mason University that focuses on market-oriented policy solutions. Troy has an extensive background in public policy and government service, including roles such as Deputy Secretary of Health and Human Services (HHS) under President George W. Bush. He has also served as a presidential historian and has written extensively on American politics, healthcare, and government operations.</p>

